Two men will appear in court tomorrow charged with the murder of a young mother - 23 years after she was last seen alive.

Nicola Payne vanished after leaving her seven-month-old baby with her boyfriend at his home to fetch baby clothes and food from her parents' home a five minute walk away.

Despite repeated searches no trace of the 18-year-old was ever found following her disappearance in Coventry, West Midlands, in December 1991.

