The teenager split her time between boyfriend Jason Cooke’s home and that of her parents, Marilyn and John nearby.

Her son, Owen, now 23, was raised by his father, who is now 43, but regularly stayed with his maternal grandparents.

Last March, West Midlands Police carried out a three-day search of woodland in the grounds of Coombe Abbey Country Park on the outskirts of Coventry.

The searches followed new information received by officers investigating Miss Payne’s disappearance. Her body has never been found.

